{"name": "xchtools", "metadata": {"name": "xchtools", "version": "0.1.15", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["dynaconf", "pymysql", "pandas", "tqdm", "requests", "pymysql-pool", "loguru"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1735722971}, "documentation": ["\n\n\n# Config\n\nIn your own project, there should be a `settings.toml` and a `.env` file.\n\n- `settings.toml` stores the common config.  \n    - To use connections module, `[default.db]` is a must.\n- `.env` stores secret things like passwords.\n\n# Usage\n\n\n## connections module\n\nmysqldb connection example toml:\n\n```toml\n[default.db]\nhost = \"replace with your host\"\nport = 3306\nuser = \"root\"\npassword = \"@format {env[MYSQLDB_PASSWORD]}\"\n```\n\nUsage in your code:\n\n```python\n\nfrom xchtools import XCHConnections\nxc = XCHConnections(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__)))\nconfig = xc.settings\nprint(config.db)\n\nxc.sql2df(\"show databases\")\n```\n\n\n```python\nfrom xchtools import ACAutomaton\nac_automaton = ACAutomaton()\nwords = [\"\u5f20\u5764\", \"\u6613\u65b9\u8fbe\", \"\u5f20\u51ef\", \"\u963f\u91cc\"]\ntext = \"\u6613\u65b9\u8fbe\u57fa\u91d1\u8fd1\u65e5\u53d1\u5e03\u4e86\u4e00\u4e2a\u667a\u80fd\u52a9\u624b\uff0c\u7531\u963f\u91cc\u4e91\u667a\u80fd\u63d0\u4f9b\u3002\"\nfor word in words:\n    ac_automaton.add_word(word)\nac_automaton.build()\nprint(ac_automaton.search(text)) \n```\n\n\n# For developer\n\n## Build and Release\n\n1. Config pypi API token `poetry config pypi-token.pypi <token>`\n2. `poetry build --format=wheel`\n3. `poetry publish`\n"], "modules": [{"name": "xchtools.funcflow", "documentation": ["%%"], "functions": [{"name": "xchtools.funcflow.add", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "a", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "ty